3A. Overview

This report is an exploratory review of counts and sizes of juvenile snowshoe hares (Lepus americanus), recorded at the Bonanza Creek Experimental Forest (US Long Term Ecological Research Site) from 1998 - 2012. This report provides analyses on juvenile hare 1) annual trap counts, 2) weight comparison and 3) relationship between weight and hind foot length. This data is important because snowshoe hares are a keystone species in northern boreal forests. The purpose of this analysis is to explore reasons that this species may experience population fluctuations.
